ENTRY       EC 1.14.13.134              Enzyme
NAME        beta-amyrin 11-oxidase;
            CYP88D6
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen;
            With NADH or NADPH as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen into the other donor
SYSNAME     beta-amyrin,NADPH:oxygen oxidoreductase (hydroxylating)
REACTION    beta-amyrin + 2 O2 + 2 NADPH + 2 H+ = 11-oxo-beta-amyrin + 3 H2O + 2 NADP+ (overall reaction) [RN:R09817];
            (1a) beta-amyrin + O2 + NADPH + H+ = 11alpha-hydroxy-beta-amyrin + H2O + NADP+ [RN:R09815];
            (1b) 11alpha-hydroxy-beta-amyrin + O2 + NADPH + H+ = 11-oxo-beta-amyrin + 2 H2O + NADP+ [RN:R09816]
ALL_REAC    R09815 R09816 R09817
SUBSTRATE   beta-amyrin [CPD:C08616];
            O2 [CPD:C00007];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080];
            11alpha-hydroxy-beta-amyrin [CPD:C19942]
PRODUCT     11-oxo-beta-amyrin [CPD:C19943];
            H2O [CPD:C00001];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006];
            11alpha-hydroxy-beta-amyrin [CPD:C19942]
COMMENT     Requires cytochrome P450. Part of the glycyrrhizin biosynthesis pathway. The enzyme is also able to oxidize 30-hydroxy-beta-amyrin to 11alpha,30-dihydroxy-beta-amyrin but this is not thought to be part of glycyrrhizin biosynthesis.
